Usage:
Add the zini directory to you fpath, either in your script or globally in ~/.zshrc.

In your script, load zini.
autoload -Uz zini

Then use zini to parse the configuration file

zini read /path/to/config/file
zini update /path/to/config/file "section" "key = value"

See https://github.com/kekePower/zini for more information